lines.text: You're not in Guatemala now, Dr. Ropata
I'm gonna end up with nothing, which is precisely what I deserve.
Come one Rachel, there's got to be a bright side to all of this.
What about all you've learnt from running your own business?
How to screw it up, you mean.
Thanks. I shall now go home and ponder my future.
Do you want a job at the clinic? While you're thinking about things?
My brain surgery's a little rusty.
As P.A. for me and David.
Thanks but I can't really see myself in a crumpling suit kissing butt in an utterly poorly-paid and meaningless form of wage slavery.
